 set aside for 10 minutes to cool. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place almonds and cashews into mixing bowl and crush <b>2 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer into a small bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place avocado oil, spring onion\/shallot, mint, lemon juice and remaining 2 teaspoons syrup into mixing bowl and combine <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b> <strong>.<\/strong> "},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and combine <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b> <strong>.<\/strong> "},{"content":"Add dressing to cooled quinoa and stir to combine. Place bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh spinach into it. Add pomegranate arils, reserved chopped nuts and roasted pumpkin. Stir gently to combine before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Go to the Thermomix in Australia YouTube channel to see a video on how to easily remove the arils from your pomegranate in your Thermomix.","If you don't follow a strict vegan diet, you can replace the maple syrup with 1½ tablespoons honey."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","4 portions"]}